name: fast-navigation
description: >
  Replace slow browser tool calls with direct HTTP fetching using httpx.
  Use for any task that reads web pages, scrapes content, checks URLs, or
  collects data from multiple sources. Achieves 30–2000x speed improvement
  over Playwright-based browser tool calls inside the Manus sandbox.

mcp_server: vaultwares-mcp
version: "1.0"
author: VaultWares

instructions: |
  When a task requires fetching web content, use these tools instead of
  the default browser tools:

  Single URL:
    Call `nav_fetch` with the target URL.
    - Set as_text=true (default) to receive clean plain text for LLM use.
    - Set as_text=false if you need the raw HTML.
    - Set ttl=0 to bypass the cache for real-time data.
    Returns: { url, status, content, error }

  Multiple URLs (parallel):
    Call `nav_fetch_many` with a list of up to 20 URLs.
    - All URLs are fetched concurrently (default 10 simultaneous).
    - Completes ~10 URLs in 1.3 s vs. 150+ s with browser tools.
    Returns: { total, succeeded, failed, results[] }

  When to fall back to the browser tool:
    - The page requires JavaScript rendering (SPA / React apps)
    - Login/session cookies are required and cannot be passed as headers
    - You need to interact with the page (click, fill forms)

  Cache behaviour:
    Results are cached for 300 s by default. Pass ttl=0 to force a fresh fetch.
